      "file_path": "test/security/check_certificates/check_certificates/check_certificates_validity.py",
      "patchset_number": 9,
      "line": 68,
      "message": "According to synopsis it's mandatory so should have \"required\" key. Also 'onap' is the default value so should have \"default='onap'\" key.\n\nAs for getting it's value from env variables argparse allows setting \"type\" key which value can be a callable so more native way to get the argument value from env is to create a function e.g. \"def get_ip()\" which will get ip from relevant env variable if not provided as argument, and then \"type=get_ip\"",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5097,
        "name": "Bartek Grzybowski",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "b.grzybowski@partner.samsung.com",
